libmobi
------------------------------------------
C library for handling Mobipocket/Kindle (MOBI) ebook format documents. Current
version supports reading and parsing functions.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.0.1-1
  cygwin-devel-2.0.1-1
  libiconv-devel-1.14-3
  libmobi-devel-0.1+git20150413-1bl1
  libmobi0-0.1+git20150413-1bl1
  libxml2-2.9.2-1
  libxml2-devel-2.9.2-1
  zlib-devel-1.2.8-3
  zlib0-1.2.8-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.18.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/bfabiszewski/libmobi

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/bfabiszewski/libmobi.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libmobi-0.1+git20150413-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libmobi-0.1+git20150413-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libmobi-0.1+git20150413-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmobi-0.1+git20150413-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmobi0-0.1+git20150413-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmobi-devel-0.1+git20150413-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libmobi)
  /usr/bin/mobitool.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libmobi.README
  /usr/share/doc/libmobi/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libmobi/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libmobi/README.md
  /usr/share/man/man1/mobitool.1.gz

(libmobi0)
  /usr/bin/cygmobi-0.dll

(libmobi-devel)
  /usr/include/mobi.h
  /usr/lib/libmobi.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libmobi.pc

